column5: Two quick things for those coming up to Lakair.  #1  If you can please bring uip something for the prize table on Saturday.  #2  If you can a salad or side dish of some sort would be nice as well for the Saturday Dinner.  Thanks!
got ya covered on both ends TJ..I have a few items for the prize table, and I will have home made cookies, potato salad, and macaroni with Tuna.  Maureen
Check and check....we have our contribution for the prize table and will bring something for the dinner as well.  Any suggestions for side dishes?  Later!
Check. Geez, I'm wearing  shorts, I hope noone wants a side of frog's legs.
Lobster is always nice  Joey
I can get some loobster...  lol
frank from bronte outdoors is going to give me some stuff and ill think of something for the food table
oh yeah ill bring the most important item too!!!!!!!!
Don't forget the stuff you need for the venison Peter, and I'll bring it.  We still on for that?  Joey
im drooling thinking about it yes we are on ...........jerky?????????????
Yes, Jerky is on my list of things to do  Joey
You smokin' Joey?????
Joey's jerky is the second best jerky I've tasted, with #1 being the Noelville butcher's.

Joey...actually, with all the Carp Bly and I have been catching, we are experimenting with a new concoction....  What does everyone think of.....  CARPCAKES????  Not sure what's in it yet, but we figured between our catches and the stuff washing up on Scugog, that we'd have lots for everyone to eat.
Joey's Jerky............sounds like a business opportunity to me............
Joey's Juicy Jerky would fetch more customers though.
Juicy jerky...........that's one to chew on.........
Joey's Juicy Jerky  and  Cliff's Carp Cakes     Are we there yet.......  Joey

I could put together a pretty mean bean salad from a favorite recipe but do you think it would be a safe thing to do ???  My niece didn't want me to make one for our trip to her place as long as Uncle Dave was coming...No explanation required...
NOOOOOOO..  ..unless of course you want to sleep outside, then bring all you want  Maureen
Beans' beans!!!  Now these I gotta try, bring em for sure  Joey
Now Joey, don't go getting carried away, unless you want to have him share your tent...remember, I'm stuck in the cabin with him  Maureen
I can't seem to locate the recipe...maybe just as well...probably take Kevin and Leslie a week to air out the campgrounds and cabins...
